```c++
#include <iostream>
#include <fstream>
#include <string>

int main() {
    std::string filename = "input.txt"; // replace with your filename
    std::string word = "example"; // replace with your word

    std::ifstream file(filename);
    if (!file) {
        std::cerr << "Failed to open the file." << std::endl;
        return 1;
    }

    std::string line;
    int count = 0;
    while (std::getline(file, line)) {
        size_t pos = 0;
        while ((pos = line.find(word, pos)) != std::string::npos) {
            count++;
            pos += word.length();
        }
    }

    std::cout << "The word \"" << word << "\" occurs " << count << " times in the file." << std::endl;

    file.close();
    return 0;
}
```

Make sure to replace "input.txt" with the name of your text file and "example" with the word you want to count.

This program opens the file specified by `filename` and reads it line by line. For each line, it searches for occurrences of the word specified by `word` using the `find` function. If a match is found, it increments the `count` variable. Finally, it prints the total count of occurrences of the word.

Note that this program assumes that the text file is in the same directory as the program. If the file is located in a different directory, you need to provide the full path to the file in `filename`.

